<recipe>
<title>
Hot Chocolate Tiramisu
</title>
<details>

</details>
<ingredients>
1/2 c . heavy whipping cream
3/4 c . granulated sugar
8 oz . package cream cheese at room temperature
1 Â¼ c . hot water
1/4 c . hot chocolate mix
3 oz . package ladyfingers
</ingredients>
<instructions>
With an electric mixer, beat whipping cream on medium speed until you can see the tracks in the whipping cream, about 3 minutes.
Add sugar, and beat until stiff peaks form.
Mix in cream cheese until combined.
In a separate small dish, stir together hot water and hot chocolate mix.
Place a small amount (about 1/4 cup) of the cream mixture in a trifle dish.
Dip ladyfingers in hot chocolate, and place in a single layer in dish.
Repeat layers, ending with cream layer.
Top with a dusting of unsweetened cocoa powder or grated chocolate.
Enjoy at room temperature or chilled.
</instructions>
</recipe>
